node.text: It can be devastating when a friend or partner betrays your trust. Even more so when in searching for reasons for the betrayal, we end up blaming ourselves. But remember that you are not to blame for other people's poor judgement or behavior.

node.text:
Drop a ❤️ below if this resonates with you👇 It's important to work on yourself and give yourself the same amount of love that you would give anyone else. This can be anything as long as it is something that winds you down or relaxes you. Even if it's taking five minutes throughout the day to breathe, it will help you get through the rest of the day. Take care of yourself and show yourself some self love today. ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
-- Jay Shetty, Co-Founder @samatea

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Jay Shetty on September 03, 2021 tagging @samatea. May be an image of 1 person, coffee cup and indoor.

node.text:
Tea has always been a huge part of my life and daily routine. It’s the first thing I drink in the morning and the last thing I drink at night. 👉 to see more⁠
⁠
One of the most powerful things about tea is the smell. Every morning before taking a sip, I take a moment to really smell it, wake up all my senses and boost my energy for the day. It sets the tone for me before I do anything, especially if it's a task. At night, when I finish dinner with Radhi I love taking a moment for myself by taking out my journal and steeping another cup of tea, reflecting on my day and expressing gratitude. Journaling and drinking tea calms my body and relaxes my thoughts before getting into bed. It's the perfect way to end my day and one of the secrets to getting a good night of sleep 💤🫖⁠
⁠

node.text:
The more you let go, the more you're able to live 💛 Comment a YES below if you love this @jayshettygenius post. ⁠
⁠
When you commit to trusting the process, you allow the universe to reveal its gifts to you. Shed your shaky anxieties and lean into the joy of not knowing. ⁠
⁠
This is what @jayshettygenius is all about 🙏⁠
⁠
We meet in weekly workshops and meditations every week to become centered, release anxiety, and allow our best selves to come forward. ⁠
⁠
I'll see you in the next @jayshettygenius workshop. Link in bio to join now! 👉 jayshettygenius.com

node.text: It can be devastating when a friend or partner betrays your trust. Even more so when in searching for reasons for the betrayal, we end up blaming ourselves. But remember that you are not to blame for other people's poor judgement or behavior.
